> As a support, your best metric on how well your doing, is who the enemy team prioritizes during a team fight. If your taking 5 ults as a support, you know your doing something right. The enemy team knows your the biggest threat to them winning! ;)


Getting focused 24/7 as {{champion:16}}
You kill me or you kill nobody

The reasons why people don't like to support are pretty simple:

* Limited playstyles and build itematizations (the primary concept arround supports is still build arround CDR>MANA REG>HP)
* Vision controle is still build arround the support (especially in low elo this is problematic)
* Not all roles and playstyles are supported in the support position
* Riot is one of the first game that gives support a more active responsibility and their still blank in that aspect
* With all these limited options that skillcap is pretty high and it wouldn't decrease in this active supportive playstyle

Their is still low interaction between all playstyles mostly when it comes to itematisation. The recent released supports {{champion:201}} & {{champion:432}} both showed a playstyle that wasn't promoted before. This said whe still have a long way to go:

* Support / Tank - {{champion:201}}
* Tank / Support - {{champion:89}}
* Tank - {{champion:12}} 
* Tank / Fighter - {{champion:53}} 
* Support / Mage - {{champion:432}} {{champion:16}} {{champion:40}} {{champion:267}} {{champion:26}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:37}}
* Mage / Support - {{champion:43}} ({{champion:143}}) ({{champion:25}})
* Mage - ({{champion:1}}) ({{champion:161}})
* Support / Fighter - {{champion:412}} {{champion:44}} 

----

It feels like depite all these new playstyle whe still have a limited acces to certain playstyle. The thing that I still miss on supports is the situation when your team lacks on magic damage. Than builds like: 

* Spellvamp builds: Whe all known spellvamp can work as a form off sustain (think about {{champion:25}})
* Mpen builds: Think about {{champion:143}} 

Could be intressting on certain poke style supports. But right now it's all build arround healing: {{champion:432}} {{champion:16}} {{champion:40}} {{champion:267}} {{champion:26}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:37}} & I seriously doubt they can cover the lack off magic damage in their kit.
